The United States amends the rules for obtaining a visa
Persons must present themselves before their conversation at the Consulate at the Service Offices for the application of a visa; the costs will be shortened.
With effect from 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa in the United States Embassy and in the Consulates are amended.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves in the Consulate at the Service Offices for Visum Application (ASC, the initial letters in English).
The ASC staff shall take up the biometric data of the applicant, which is checked by the Consulate before the conversation.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total costs for the settlement of the visa are declined, as the date agreement is no longer necessary to pay separately the processing of the visa application and the transport service provided by the document.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the contrary to $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visa with application (including visa for time workers) and $390 for hands and investors.
Those who just want to extend their visa do not have to conduct any conversation in the consulate, they only have to imagine the next ASC where they are presenting their documents and taking their fingerprints.
Since the biometric data are collected in the ASC, applicants who need a second date for the conversation in the Consulate remain there less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo do not have to pay the service charge of $26 anymore.
For further information on the new visa application procedure, see the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
